div1.p:
There arose a little Debate about the Signing [
Ralph Morrison
] the Council for the Defendant urg'd, that it could not be prov'd to be R. Morrison; but Mr Jesse was present, and gave Oath, That what remain'd of the Name he knew to be wrote by Mr Morrison, one of the Cashiers of the Bank; and also prov'd, that it was proper and customary to tear off part of the Name as the Note was paid at the Bank.
